fields.no_info_description: Research did not identify any pertinent information on affiliated individuals or entities.
fields.name: Red Flag Check
fields.description: Affiliated individuals and/or corporate entities are screened for top-level adverse information through a variety of sanctions, watchlists, adverse media, and U.S. public record sources.

fields.no_info_description: Searches through available records did not yield any pertinent information.
fields.name: U.S. Public Records Check
fields.description: Searches are conducted through multiple commercial databases and original records to uncover pertinent information. Not all records are available online, so local inquiries may be required.

fields.no_info_description: In-depth research through multiple social media sources did not yield any relevant information.
fields.name: Social Media Intelligence (SOCMINT) Collection
fields.description: Multiple U.S. and international social media platforms are reviewed to identify derogatory, or otherwise relevant, information. Critical findings can be indexed and forensically captured.

fields.no_info_description: In-depth open source research did not yield any actionable intelligence.
fields.name: Data Removal
fields.description: Cyber Intelligence Analysts attempt to remove a subject's name, phone number, physical address, email address, and other details from online data brokers. Prescient uses an "online hardening" strategy designed to reduce the volume of publicly visible personal information, while increasing the level of complexity needed to target the subject.

fields.no_info_description: Local investigative operations are ongoing. This report will be updated as soon as findings are received.
fields.name: Local Investigative Operations
fields.description: Prescient accesses an international network of vetted investigators, many of whom are former intelligence community and law enforcement professionals, to conduct on-the-ground investigations around the world that obtain information not available via open sources or fill critical intelligence gaps.

fields.no_info_description: Research through available sources did not yield any pertinent information.
fields.name: Dark Web Intelligence Collection
fields.description: This service category represents a summation of historical and real-time cyber threat data found in sources not readily available on the surface web. Research covers the Deep Web (derived sources), the Dark Web (hidden TOR services), Pastebins (public repositories of stolen information), IRCs (instant messaging channels for hackers), information indexed by Dark Web search engines, Dark Web forums and online communities, and targeted searches for documents by type and service.

fields.no_info_description: Research into available sources did not yield any pertinent information.
fields.name: Open Source Intelligence (OSINT) Collection
fields.description: This service category represents a summation of data collected from publicly available sources, known as “open sources.” It provides a comprehensive overview of information indexed by open web search engines using customized Boolean search logic.

fields.no_info_description: Research did not yield any pertinent findings.
fields.name: Intelligence Analysis
fields.description: Raw intelligence is analytically assessed by trained Subject Matter Experts (SMEs), who evaluate relevant findings related to significant individuals and/or organizations of interest.

fields.no_info_description: The subject’s identity could not be confirmed using the Social Security Number (SSN) provided. An SSN Trace was conducted, but did not yield any results.
fields.name: Social Security Number Trace
fields.description: A search, based on the social security number, that extracts and confirms identifying information, such as full name, aliases, variations of names, date of birth and jurisdictions.

fields.no_info_description: Research through databases of federal criminal and Federal Bureau of Prisons (BOP) records did not yield any results for the subject.
fields.name: Federal Criminal Records
fields.description: Multiple legal sources are accessed and reviewed that cover Federal Cases & Dockets, Agency Decisions, Verdicts and Law Reviews. In addition, Public Records are reviewed to include criminal records, Department of Correction records, Criminal Court records and Arrest Records.

fields.no_info_description: Research through multiple databases did not yield any information for the subject.
fields.name: State and County Criminal Records
fields.description: Multiple legal sources are accessed and reviewed that cover State Cases & Dockets, Agency Decisions, Verdicts and Law Reviews. In addition, Public Records are reviewed to include criminal records, Department of Correction records, Criminal Court records and Arrest Records.

fields.name: County Criminal Case Search
fields.description: County records are accessed and reviewed based on specific county information provided. Based on the jurisdiction, which may be assigned to a city or county name, information from local Superior, Municipal and/or District court information is reviewed.

fields.no_info_description: Research through multiple databases did not yield any information for the subject.
fields.name: Motor Vehicle Search
fields.description: Driving records are reviewed to include minor traffic violations, misdemeanors, felonies and DUI’s.

fields.no_info_description: Research on the Sexual Offender Registry and National Sex Offender Public Website (NSOPW) did not yield any results for the subject.
fields.name: Sexual Offenders Search
fields.description: A search is conducted against the Sex Offender Registry for all 50 states (plus Washington, D.C.).

fields.name: Global Professional/Business Reference Check
fields.description: Professional/Business references that are provided (or obtained from the corporate security questionnaire) are conducted with individuals or businesses located throughout the world.  A third-party individual or corporate entity’s background is verified and assessed based on specific criteria defined by your organization.

fields.name: Education Verification
fields.description: A verification through public records data sources and/or direct verification from previous educational institutes is conducted.

fields.name: I-9 Verification
fields.description: An applicant's work eligibility is verified through DHS and SSA databases.

fields.no_info_description: The subject was screened against more than 26,000 licensed news sources from international, national, and regional outlets, although no adverse information was discovered.
fields.name: Global Media/Negative News Profile
fields.description: Individuals are screened against over 26,000 licensed news sources from international, national and regional outlets. Sources include: newspapers, newswires, press releases, magazines, trade publications, broadcast transcripts and more. Searches are conducted against 100 variations of the following key words: Bribery, Corruption, Unethical, Criminal, Court and Violation. Negative News is identified from these searches as potential “red flags” that should be considered in the due diligence process.

fields.no_info_description: The subject was cross-referenced through open-source searches and social media to identify criminal and/or unethical activity; however, no results were found.
fields.name: Open Source (Discovery)
fields.description: An analytic search through open sources to identify and isolate component information of a subject and/or entity. Various open sources and social media outlets are reviewed, utilizing online tools and unique search strings, to discover personal and professional information, business activities and/or relationships. This specialized search and analysis verifies current information provided and discovers new information that may have not been identified through traditional database checks.

fields.no_info_description: The subject was screened against multiple PEP lists and cross-referenced with more than 1.4 million PEP profiles, although no information was discovered.
fields.name: Politically Exposed Persons (PEP) Screen
fields.description: Individuals are screened against PEP lists of multiple providers in order to identify service to a public function or ties to such person that, by the virtue of their position and influence, presents higher risk for potential corrupt activity, including bribery. Our access to PEP lists includes 1.4 million profiles, as well as family members and associates.

fields.no_info_description: The subject was screened against more than 800 sanctions and watch lists from more than 75 countries, although no information was discovered.
fields.name: Global Sanctions and Watch List Review
fields.description: Individuals being researched are screened against more than 800 sanctions and watchlists, which include (but are not limited to): Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC) list, Department of State, Directorate of Defense Trade Controls, Consolidated List of Debarred Parties, International Police Most Wanted and Red Alerts, FBI Most Wanted Lists and many more.

fields.no_info_description: The subject was cross-referenced against cases – civil and criminal – from international courts spanning the United States, the European Union, Ireland, Northern Ireland, Scotland, England, Wales, Canada, Malaysia, Brunei, Hong Kong, Australia, New Zealand, and South Africa, although no adverse information was discovered.
fields.name: International, Federal and State Legal Source Review
fields.description: Multiple legal sources are checked that cover Cases & Dockets, Agency Decisions, Verdicts and Law Reviews. Cases include decided court cases – civil and criminal – from state, federal and international courts. Dockets provide additional coverage of Federal and State courts, including pending matters.  Agency decisions combine opinions, orders, enforcement actions, no-action/interpretive/exemptive letters, decrees, judgments and rulings from various government agencies. Jury Verdicts and Settlements provide access to selected online verdict and settlement information for civil cases across the United States. Law Reviews help explain cases and the facts in dispute.

fields.name: Business Profile Review
fields.description: A review of Company Reports, including Dun & Bradstreet Global (D&B) Global Profiles, covering both public and private companies, and spanning 220 countries in developed and emerging markets. Corporate hierarchies and parent subsidiary structures are reviewed to identify individuals, past business and/or current activity that may pose as a “red flag” within the organization.

fields.name: Biographical Source Review
fields.description: Biographical analysis is conducted to reveal key facts about an individual, which include (but are not limited to) – personal information, career history, educational background, participation in civic or philanthropic organizations, awards and more. Sources include: Standard & Poor’s Corporate Register of Directors & Executives, U.S. Executive Compensation Database, Gale Biographies, Who’s Who Biographies and more.

fields.name: Personal Reference Check
fields.description: An interview is conducted with personal references to verify and assess an applicant’s ability. The questions and answers provided below are based specifically on your company’s human resource guidance.

fields.name: Corporate Security Questionnaire
fields.description: Third parties are directly engaged to provide responses for the corporate security questionnaire that is crafted with your organization, to verify and assess an individual or corporate entity’s background. The questions and answers provided are based specifically on your organization’s compliance guidance.

fields.name: Address Verification and History
fields.description: A public records verification of all address history and dates associated with identifying information.

fields.no_info_description: Research through multiple databases did not yield any information for the subject.
fields.name: Bankruptcies, Judgments & Liens Search
fields.description: Bankruptcies, Judgments and Liens from all 50 states, D.C. and select territories are obtained and reviewed.

fields.name: Employment History
fields.description: Discovery of previous employment through public records and/or open source data sources.The subject’s provided employment information was verified, as outlined in the Employment Verification service category. Open source and public records research did not uncover any additional employment history details.

fields.name: Military/Federal Service Verification
fields.description: A verification through public records data sources and/or direct verification from previous military/federal service branches is conducted.

fields.name: Comprehensive Public Records Check
fields.description: An all-in-one public records assessment is conducted to assess and/or verify background information such as individual identifiers (full name, aliases, SSN, DOB), current and historical addresses, criminal filings, bankruptcies, liens, judgments, business connections, property ownership, licenses and/or potential relatives.

fields.name: Oral Drug Screening Service (5-Panel)
fields.description: Oral Fluids drug testing check for Amphetamines, Cocaine, Opiates, Phencyclidine and Marijuana is conducted.

fields.name: Oral Drug Screening Service (9-Panel + Oxycodone)
fields.description: Oral Fluids drug-testing check for Amphetamines, Cocaine, Opiates, Phencyclidine, Marijuana, Barbiturates, Benzodiazepines, Propoxyphene, Methadone and Oxycodone is conducted.

fields.name: Urinalysis Drug Screening Service (10-Panel)
fields.description: Urine drug-testing check for Amphetamines, Cocaine, Opiates, Phencyclidine, Marijuana, Barbiturates, Benzodiazepines, Propoxyphene, Methadone, and Methaqualone. A Specimen Validity Test is included in the panel. This package is bundled to include both the test screen and confirmation test.

fields.name: Urinalysis Drug Screening Service (10-Panel + Alcohol)
fields.description: Urine drug testing check for Amphetamines, Cocaine, Opiates, Phencyclidine, Marijuana, Barbiturates, Benzodiazepines, Propoxyphene, Methadone, Methaqualone and Alcohol. A Specimen Validity Test is included in the panel. This package is bundled to include both the test screen and confirmation test.

fields.name: Full-Scope Background Review
fields.description: An enhanced search through open sources and social media outlets is conducted, utilizing online tools and unique search strings, to discover personal and professional information, global business activities and/or personal relationships. This specialized search and analysis verifies current information provided and discovers new information that may have not been previously identified.

fields.name: Open Source (Deep-Dive)
fields.description: A holistic search that focuses on defining the entire background of an entity and/or subject by researching variables pertinent to the entity/subject, relationships of the variables, and the effects of each variable on the situation. This service category provides advanced investigation tactics for business activities that may have significant risk involved and therefore require the highest level of analysis and review.

fields.no_info_description: The subject was screened against more than 800 sanctions and watch lists from more than 75 countries, although no information was discovered.
fields.name: Sanctions & Watch List Review
fields.description: Individual names and/or corporations are screened against more than 800 sanctions and watch lists from more than 75 countries translated from multiple languages. Some of the information included involves white-collar crimes, crimes against humanity, terrorist threats, disqualified directors and debarred companies and more. A small sample of lists includes: Crimestoppers, the Office of Foreign Office (OFAC) list, Her Majesty’s Treasury Consolidated List, European Union Designated Terrorists Consolidated List, International Police Most Wanted and Red Alerts, United Nations Consolidated List and many more.

fields.no_info_description: The subject was cross-referenced against cases – civil and criminal – from international courts spanning multiple countries, although no adverse information was discovered.
fields.name: International Legal Source Review
fields.description: Cases, also known as case law, are reviewed that cover decided court cases – civil and criminal – from international courts spanning the European Union, Ireland, Northern Ireland, Scotland, England, Wales, United States, Canada, Malaysia, Brunei, Hong Kong, Australia, New Zealand and South Africa.

fields.name: Global Professional Reference Check
fields.description: Professional reference checks conducted with individuals or businesses located throughout the world. SpotLit will verify and assess an individual's background based on specific criteria requested by our clients.

fields.name: Security Questionnaire
fields.description: Our team works with your organization to craft a customized security questionnaire to verify and assess an individual’s background. The questions and answers provided are based specifically on your company’s compliance guidance to identify any activity or relationships that may pose as “red flags” for your organization.

fields.name: Employment Review
fields.description: A review of employment activity through data sources and/or direct verification of previous employers is conducted. Insight into past employment validates information on a CV/Resume.

fields.name: Address Verification
fields.description: A verification of all address history and dates associated with identifying information is conducted utilizing database sources and/or direct verification.

fields.name: Establish Identity
fields.description: An initial investigative check to authenticate identifiers of an individual. This includes: social security number (or personal identification number) validation, a cross check of the individual’s date/place of birth against local government records and verification that the individual identity is not stolen.

fields.name: Verify Personal and Business Address/Phone
fields.description: A verification of personal and business information is conducted in country. Local phone registration records are reviewed for registrant and location. In addition, address history, employment locations and time periods documented on an individual’s resume/C.V. are validated.

fields.name: Confirm Tax ID Number
fields.description: Confirmation of an individual’s tax ID number is conducted. Our investigators verify the individual is registered in the tax system and check with sources to identify tax liens and/or revenue actions.

fields.name: Review Source of Wealth
fields.description: The source and allocation of an individual’s funds are scrutinized to ensure finances are consistent with personal and business practices. This includes: conducting hard-asset searches for property, vehicle(s), aircraft(s) and vessels, verifying financial, personal and business assets, and identifying financial accounts.

fields.name: Validate Previous Employers
fields.description: To verify and validate employment, investigators identify current and past employers, cross check address history with location of employment and, when appropriate, check employers for current and past criminal activity.

fields.name: Confirm Corporate Affiliations and Associations
fields.description: Confirmation of all business affiliations and associations is conducted with appropriate Department of State resources on location. In addition, LinkedIn and other social media sources are reviewed to identify loose association with private and public entities.

fields.name: Conduct Criminal and Civil Checks
fields.description: In addition to database research and analysis, on-the-ground investigations into federal, state and local records, and criminal and civil checks are conducted on an individual and/or corporate entity. Local sources are contacted to identify criminal investigations that did not result in arrest or charges, and therefore may not appear in open-source searches.

fields.name: Review Judgments, Bankruptcies and Liens
fields.description: Local records with the Clerk of the Courts are accessed to identify current and past Judgments and Liens. In addition, federal court checks are conducted to identify bankruptcy cases.

fields.name: Determine Character Profile
fields.description: In order to effectively assess an individual’s character profile, investigators identify industry sources to obtain reputational information, conduct specific media checks to establish public reputation of target(s), and initiate contact with trusted sources.

fields.name: Identify Family Members / Associates
fields.description: Background checks into an individual’s social networks and corporate records are conducted to identify close family members and business associates. Information from the target’s resume/C.V. is also reviewed and validated.

fields.name: Enhanced PEP Screen
fields.description: An enhanced investigation to determine PEP affiliation. Information received through media checks is collated with additional investigative services that include – identification of political contributions, relationships to corporate affiliated entities and direct ties to government contracts. In addition, investigators initiate contact with trusted political figures, where appropriate, to specifically identify association with political figures, and collate information and data to evaluate the position and affiliations of the individual to make a rational decision of PEP implications.

fields.name: Identify Contacts Inside / Outside the Government
fields.description: Investigators initiate contact with trusted sources in the law enforcement and prosecutorial communities to gather confidential information about an individual and their affiliations with illicit activities. In addition, investigators will initiate contact with sources in regulatory agencies to gather amplifying information. Based on contacts and sources identified, investigators will identify and collect any new relevant data.

fields.name: Conduct a Discreet Site Survey
fields.description: To uncover new information or verify current information, a discreet site survey is conducted. This includes: conducting physical checks of locations pertinent to the inquiry, making an evaluation on whether the location appropriately coincides with what would be expected for the individual or corporate entity, initiating contact with trusted law enforcement personnel to identify reports alleging wrongdoing by savory characters, identifying vehicles and license tag numbers and, when appropriate, obtaining photographs of assets and individuals.

fields.name: Corporate Records Check
fields.description: To validate a corporate entity, investigators review Department of State records, check for filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), conduct reviews related to licensure for bonds & securities (i.e. Series 7 License), and initiate contact with domestic and international partners for adverse or disciplinary actions.

fields.name: Corporate Regulatory Office Check
fields.description: A review with federal, state and local regulatory agencies is conducted. Investigators identify any information reported to these entities that is directly or indirectly related to the corporate entity under review.

fields.name: Interviews with Associates
fields.description: Direct contact and interviews are conducted with personnel that have direct ties to a corporate entity, to include prior opposing litigants, past affiliations, former employees and close associates. Investigators identify, locate and interview individuals in a position to provide information and evidence pertinent to the target, to uncover information detailing items of interest.

fields.name: Professional Reference Check
fields.description: An interview is conducted with professional references to verify and assess an applicant’s ability. The questions are based specifically on your company’s Human Resource guidance.

fields.name: Employment Verification
fields.description: Direct verification from previous employers is conducted, based on past employment information provided by the client and/or employee.

fields.no_info_description: HUMINT collection efforts yielded little to no relevant information.
fields.name: Human Intelligence Collection (HUMINT)
fields.description: A written summary of the results of intelligence gathering activity, classified as “raw intelligence.” This service provides a concise, focused overview of information gathered in the field.

fields.name: Social Media (Deep-Dive)
fields.description: A comprehensive social media investigation is conducted on the subject to capture time and preserve all social media evidence for legal forensic record purposes. Forensic record includes case-centric workflow from search and collection, through production, in searchable native format, that preserves critical metadata and ensures information is accurate at the time of collection.

fields.name: Social Media (Discovery)
fields.description: A social media scrape is conducted to authenticate and index social media content from the publicly available information of targeted users. Unique search strings are crafted for the subject’s name and suspected name variations, to identify derogatory information and activity posted, tweeted, uploaded or pinned by the subject.
